oldentry: Popular explanation: making a tennis serve.
verblex: 2. To throw up the ball in tennis and hit it to start play. English = serve.
nomlex: 1. A game played by two or four players on a rectangular court. They use rackets to hit a ball over a net which is between them. English = tennis.
2. The beginning of play in tennis when someone throws up the ball and hits it. English = serve.
